product_name: NYX Professional MakeupMicro Brow Pencil Vegan Eyebrow Pencil
summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsCruelty FreeVeganGive BackNYX Professional Makeup Micro Brow Pencil does it all - A micro mechanical eyebrow pencil that shapes, defines and fills in sparse brows for a natural look.
details: DetailsBenefitsMicro mechanical eyebrow pencil with a dual-ended spoolie & colored pencil, a 2-in-1 eyebrow shaper & eyebrow tint for easy brow care so you can step up your eyebrow makeup gameFeatures a creamy, longwear brow formulaThe super-skinny tip draws ultra-fine lines coating even the finest hairs, allowing you to create the look of natural brow hairs in just a flick of the wristThis bestselling brow pencil is your go-to weapon, whether you need to define sparse brows or tame unruly hairsThis vegan eyebrow pencil is available in 8 shades to compliment all eyebrow shadesVegan formula (no animal-derived ingredient or by-product)Cruelty freeItem 2284049How To UseCreate a more defined brow by filling in areas that may be sparse or over-tweezed with the Micro Brow Pencil. Use short strokes to help create the appearance of fuller brows. Use the spoolie end to brush and blend for a more natural look.Pro Tip: When choosing a brow color, go close to the shade of your natural roots.IngredientsPolyethylene, C12-15 Alkyl Ethylhexanoate, Hydrogenated Coco-Glycerides, Ozokerite, Polyglyceryl-2 Triisostearate, C20-40 Alcohols, Euphorbia Cerifera (Candelilla) Wax/Candelilla Cera/Cire De Candelilla, Zinc Stearate, Microcrystalline Wax/Cera Microcristallina/Cire Microcrystalline, Dimethicone, Sorbitan Tristearate, Tocopheryl Acetate, Glyceryl Caprylate. May Contain: Mica, Titanium Dioxide (Ci 77891), Iron Oxides (Ci 77491, 77492, 77499), Ferric Ammonium Ferrocyanide (Ci 77510).
how_to_use: Create a more defined brow by filling in areas that may be sparse or over-tweezed with the Micro Brow Pencil. Use short strokes to help create the appearance of fuller brows. Use the spoolie end to brush and blend for a more natural look.Pro Tip: When choosing a brow color, go close to the shade of your natural roots.
ingredients: Euphorbia Cerifera (Candelilla) Wax/Candelilla Cera/Cire De Candelilla

faceoff_positive.comments: I've used powders, waxes, shadow, and all kinds of pencils. I've been growing my brows out for over a year now (slow going thanks to years of overplucking) and still have major sparse areas. A few swipes with the spoolie, soft "line" just above and below brows, then fill in...spoolie quickly again to soften color, and tiny bit of wax to keep them set. I did both in less than 5 minutes, and also used the NYX "magic" pencil to highlight/clean up. Highly recommend both! Side note - I was really unsure what color to get. I'm a natural light/medium ash brunette, but I dye it much darker. I hate any orange/red tones, and taupes just kinda of look "off." I got the ash brown pencil, and it's PERFECT!
faceoff_positive.headline: Great little pencil!

faceoff_negative.comments: I was super excited to see this new product! Finally an affordable mechanical pencil! I purchased the color blonde and auburn. I was very disappointed with the colors. The color blonde was extremely yellow! My hair color is blonde and I usually use ABH brow wiz in taupe. And that is even a little too dark for me. But the NYX blonde looked terrible. Borderline high lighter yellow! There is no "ash blonde" or "taupe" just a scary yellow lol. As for the auburn color. It was ok. I used it in my sister. She is a red head. I had to put a darker powder over it. It is good for a light red head. The quality of the pencils are great! The colors need major improvement!
faceoff_negative.headline: Great product quality. Bad colors
